3. SEED (6) — IDENTITY TRACKING ROOT

A Seed is not a wallet identity.
It is:
a shared tracking container for multiple addresses that voluntarily associate with it
Seed properties
created from origin address (hash-based)
tracks all addresses that declare or join it
does NOT control funds
does NOT execute transactions
Seed function
Tracks:
address participation history
mint flows involving its members
cross-Seed interactions
Prime membership relations



4. PRIME (9) — CLUSTER SYSTEM

A Prime is:
a cluster of Seeds
recursive grouping of groups
structural layer of the identity graph
Prime behavior
contains Seeds
contains other Primes
forms recursive nested clusters
Prime meaning
Represents:
organization
coherence
or decay of structure



5. WAVE (0) — GOVERNANCE FIELD

A Wave is:
governance action object
